Package gw.api.bean.compare.ui

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BaseEntityDiffDisplay<T extends KeyableBean>  
    BasePropertyDiffDisplay  
    DiffDisplay
    Represents a policy difference as it appears in the policy refresh comparison screen. It provides everything necessary to display the difference. Operations on a DiffDisplay are not recursive, for example {@link #getType()} does not examine their children.
    DiffDisplay.Type  
    DiffDisplayFactory  
    DiffDisplayUI  
    EntityDiffDisplay<T extends KeyableBean>
    Superclass for displaying entity diffs in the policy refresh comparison UI. This class can be used as is or subclassed by customers to give control over the UI or to add errors and warnings. If customers do not specify any particular {@link gw.api.bean.compare.EntityDiff} type for an entity type then this is the type that will be used by default.
    HierarchicalDiff<T extends DiffDisplay>
    Specifies a hierarchical relationship between {@link DiffDisplay} instances.
    HierarchicalDiffDelegate<T extends DiffDisplay>  
    PropertyDiffDisplay
    Superclass for displaying property diffs in the policy refresh comparison UI. This class can be used as is or subclassed by customers to give more control over the UI. There is no direct mechanism for customers to specifytheir own subclass (or alternative implementation) for PropertyDiffDisplay. The only approach at the moment is to override the {@link HierarchicalDiff#addChild(DiffDisplay)} method in the DiffDisplay object used to display an entity (typically some subclass of {@link gw.api.bean.compare.ui.EntityDiffDisplay}). The addChild method can then watch for incoming children of type PropertyDiffDisplay and replace them with a custom subtype or alternative type.
